## Timeline of Key Events

| Year | Event |
|------|-------|
| 1961 | Born December 7, Hong Kong |
| 1984 | Graduated HKU, translation degree |
| 1985 | Entered Cantopop as lyricist under 林振強 |
| Late 1980s | First major collaborations: 張國榮, 梅艷芳 |
| 1990s | Begins extensive work with 王菲, 林憶蓮, 張學友 |
| 1995 | Begins 9-year consecutive Lyricist of Year run at 叱咤樂壇 |
| 1998 | Major heartbreak + Buddhist conversion; 王菲 marriage troubles witnessed |
| 1999 | 《紅豆》 released; Golden Melody Award Best Lyricist |
| 2003 | End of first consecutive award run (9 years) |
| 2006 | 《富士山下》 for Eason Chan; 2006–2009 second award run begins |
| 2010 | Second Golden Melody Award Best Lyricist |
| 2010s | Anxiety disorder publicly disclosed; mental health advocacy |
| 2014 | Umbrella Movement; political stance solidifies |
| 2017 | Blacklisted in mainland China |
| 2021 | Taiwanese citizenship obtained |

